==English==

{{rank|spoke|strange|force|464|character|taking|information|seem}}

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''kharacter''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[being]] [[involve]]d in the [[action]] of a [[story]].
# A [[symbol]] used to [[represent]] a [[sound]] or a [[word]].
# A [[distinguish]]ing [[feature]]; [[characteristic]]; A complex of mental and ethical traits marking a person or a group.
# A [[moral]] [[strength]].
#:''"You may not like to eat liver," said Calvin's father, "but it builds '''character'''."''
# A person with many [[notable]] or [[eccentric]] [[feature]]s.
# {{mathematics}} A [[complex number]] representing an element of a [[finite]] [[Abelian]] [[group]].

